[package]
name = "hyprpaper"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "hyprpaper — wallpaper daemon config (shares ~/.config/hypr with hyprland)"

[[link]]
source = ".config/hypr/hyprpaper.conf"
target = ".config/hypr/hyprpaper.conf"

---

# hyprpaper

One file. Lives under `~/.config/hypr/` (the shared hyprland
namespace) alongside `hyprland.conf`. When the `hyprland`
package gets a manifest later, it'll add rows in the same
target directory — no conflict, hapi only owns explicit
[[link]] rows.
